  "prompt": "How to develop an exit strategy?",
  "response": "Developing an exit strategy involves several key steps:\n\n1. Business Goals\n- Define long-term objectives\n- Determine desired outcome (sale, succession, merger)\n- Set financial targets\n\n2. Timing Considerations\n- Assess current market conditions\n- Evaluate business valuation\n- Consider personal and professional readiness\n\n3. Valuation Methods\n- Professional business appraisal\n- Asset-based valuation\n- Revenue multiple approach\n- Earnings multiple method\n\n4. Potential Exit Options\n- Sell to external buyer\n- Transfer to family members\n- Management buyout\n- Initial public offering (IPO)\n- Liquidation\n- Merger/acquisition\n\n5. Financial Preparation\n- Clean up financial statements\n- Reduce debt\n- Improve profitability\n- Organize financial documentation\n- Build consistent revenue streams\n\n6. Legal Considerations\n- Consult with lawyers\n- Review contracts\n- Understand tax implications\n- Protect intellectual property\n\n7. Succession Planning\n- Identify potential successors\n- Train replacement leadership\n- Develop transition plan\n\n8. Professional Advisory Team\n- Engage financial advisor\n- Hire business broker\n- Consult tax professional\n- Work with legal counsel\n\n9. Continuous Refinement\n- Regularly review and update strategy\n- Monitor market conditions\n- Remain flexible",
